description.narrative: By 2021, regional and national institutions and partners in selected countries (subject to change) have improved capacities on public advocacy, policy/plan and multisectoral coordination., which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Every woman, newborn, child and adolescent has an equal chance to survive and thrive

description.narrative: WCARO provided leadership to partners and countries to keep on track with commitments;on;prevention and treatment of all forms of malnutrition. A;range of advocacy;and;policy products were developed and disseminated;for;countries;to;adapt and scale up service delivery targeting the;most;marginalized;in all contexts. This resulted in;sustained progress in the roll out;of regional initiatives;including;Stronger;With;Breastmilk Only, First Foods,;Food;Fortification, Vitamin A supplementation, WASH and Nutrition, Simplified Approaches for the treatment of wasting, supply systems;and;the Global Action Plan (GAP) for the prevention and care of wasting | Status:Met | As-of Date:17/01/2022
